5. CONCLUSION & FUTURE SCOPE OF WORK
â€¢ We observed that the graph for the Negative binomial with D differed from graphs of other distributions in the original implementation. The log-likelihood curve for the former decreases with increase in number of change points. Further analysis is required to assert whether the graph above is as intended or should it be similar to others.
â€¢ A fix in the original implementation can render the graph (Negative binomial with D) similar to other graphs. This behavior has been documented in our code.
â€¢ The code can be further refactored and should be taken up in the future versions.
â€¢ The current code does not take into account the penalty for increasing the number of domains. Future versions of the code can assign a penalty for increases in the number of domains.
